        <li><a href="#luxury-picks" style="color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 500;">&rarr; Top Luxury Picks (5-Star)</a></li>
        <li><a href="#mid-range" style="color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 500;">&rarr; Best Mid-Range Options</a></li>
        <li><a href="#budget-apartments" style="color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 500;">&rarr; Budget &amp; Serviced Apartments</a></li>
        <li><a href="#transport-logistics" style="color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 500;">&rarr; Stadium Transport Logistics</a></li>
        <li><a href="#faqs" style="color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 500;">&rarr; Frequently Asked Questions</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <!-- ARTICLE BODY -->
    <article style="font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--white-dim); line-height: 1.8;">
      
      <h2 id="introduction" style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2.25rem; color: var(--gold); margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">1. Strategic Logistics Overview: Preparing for the Crowds</h2>
      <p>
        Securing the right lodging is the single most critical decision for fans traveling to Riyadh for the historic FIFA World Cup 2034. As the capital prepares to host forty-eight teams and thousands of international spectators, traffic management around major sports complexes will be highly regulated. Staying in close proximity to the premier venues, particularly the massive King Fahd International Stadium (known locally as "The Pearl"), is vital for a smooth, stress-free travel experience.
      </p>
      <p>
        By selecting accommodation within a short driving distance or directly connected via the automated metro lines, visitors can bypass the post-match highway gridlocks that frequently occur after major tournaments. Furthermore, choosing a base that offers a balance of stadium proximity and metropolitan lifestyle is key to experiencing Riyadh's culinary, retail, and historical wonders.
      </p>
      <p style="background: var(--surface2); padding: 1.25rem 1.75rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--gold); border-radius: 4px; font-style: italic; margin: 2rem 0;">
        ⚽ <strong>Need match tickets, transit tips, or stadium details?</strong> Read our detailed <a href="/fifa-2034/" style="color: var(--gold); text-decoration: underline; font-weight: 600;">Saudi Arabia FIFA World Cup 2034 Guide</a> for the ultimate fan walkthrough.
      </p>

      <h2 id="why-stay-here" style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2.25rem; color: var(--gold); margin-top: 3.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">2. Why Stay Near King Fahd Stadium?</h2>
      <p>
        King Fahd International Stadium is located in the eastern district of Riyadh, an area that enjoys smooth highway connectivity to the city's commercial hubs. Staying nearby offers several distinct advantages for football tourists and business travelers:
      </p>
      <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.8rem;">
        <li>
          <strong>Proximity to Match Days:</strong> Bypassing the heavy traffic flow along major highways during peak match days. A short 5-to-10 minute commute allows you to reach the security gates ahead of the crowds.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Central Access to Olaya District:</strong> Olaya serves as the upscale financial and retail heart of modern Riyadh. Selecting a hotel in this zone provides a central base surrounded by high-end shopping malls (like Kingdom Centre and Centria), gourmet dining, and lively evening cafes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Direct Metro Connectivity:</strong> The Riyadh Metro operates key routes that service both Olaya and the stadium sectors. With easy access to Metro Line 2 (Red Line) and Line 1 (Blue Line), travelers can transit between modern shopping hubs, hotels, and the stadium gates without relying on cars.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="comparison-table" style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2.25rem; color: var(--gold); margin-top: 3.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">3. Hotel Comparison Matrix</h2>
      <p>
        Below is a comparison table outlining the key features, ratings, and logistical details for the top recommended lodging options close to the stadium:
      </p>

      <div style="overflow-x: auto; margin: 2rem 0; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px;">
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; min-width: 600px; text-align: left; background: var(--surface2); font-size: 0.95rem;">
